  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Construction) #79387",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Design and Build Service Provider</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Quantity Surveyor</strong></li><li>Working Location: North - Admiralty</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days / Mon-Fri: 9am-6pm, Sat: 9am-1pm</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Up to SGD 4000 + AWS + Performance Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Source quotations, perform price comparisons, and prepare costing summaries.</li><li>Develop comprehensive project costings.</li><li>Prepare tender and contract documentation.</li><li>Collaborate with the project team on variation works, progress claims, and cost control.</li><li>Coordinate with main contractors, subcontractors, clients, and suppliers/vendors on project cost-related matters.</li><li>Oversee and manage document control processes.</li><li>Handle all quantity surveying (QS) reporting responsibilities.</li><li>Conduct risk assessments and cost calculations.</li><li>Perform tender analysis and assist in finalizing contract sums.</li><li>Manage internal budget controls, providing advice on cost limits and budget adherence.</li><li>Negotiate contracts effectively.</li><li>Assess contractor claims and provide guidance on contractual disputes.</li><li>Conduct cost analysis for construction activities.</li><li>Work with the purchasing manager to evaluate procurement strategies and recommend cost-effective solutions.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Quantity Surveying / Engineering</li><li>Min. 1 year of working experience in the construction industry</li><li>Skilled in quantity take-off, cost control, progress claim preparation, and contract administration, with proficiency in AutoCAD</li><li>Familiar with MS Office Applications (Word, Excel & PowerPoint)</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79387 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
